        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(qa): wire Crabline fake provider env",
        "body": "## Summary\n- pass Crabline-provided gateway env into QA Lab spawned runtimes\n- route Slack Web API calls to Crabline via `SLACK_API_URL` / `channels.slack.apiUrl`\n- register WhatsApp socket factory wiring for Crabline-backed QA runs\n- map Crabline WhatsApp manifests to OpenClaw-facing `WHATSAPP_API_ROOT` / `WHATSAPP_ACCESS_TOKEN` during QA runs\n- update QA Lab to the published `@openclaw/crabline@0.1.3` release\n\n## Why\nCrabline now publishes the Slack fake provider server, WhatsApp runtime socket factory, and WhatsApp recorder ID-parity fixes in `v0.1.3`. This PR consumes that published package from QA Lab while keeping the OpenClaw channel plugin interfaces generic: OpenClaw reads normal provider API/socket env, and QA Lab fills those values from Crabline when the `crabline` channel driver is selected.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`\n- `pnpm vitest run extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions`",
